 "HHGoodsRentalOpsAdvisor ⊣ HHGoodsRentalGovernor
 (`hgrentalops.governor`), langgraph-clj StateGraph
 (langgraph.graph, hgrentalops.operation/build), append-only audit
 ledger (hgrentalops.store/ledger + append-ledger!, MemStore).
 A genuinely compiled StateGraph (:intake -> :advise -> :govern ->
 :decide -+-> :commit / :request-approval -> :commit / :hold) with
 interrupt-before #{:request-approval} + in-memory checkpointer for
 real human-in-the-loop resume. A back-office OPERATIONS COORDINATION
 actor for the household-goods rental fleet (furniture/appliances/
 party-event equipment): rental-record logging (checkout/return/
 inspection-note), fleet-operation/delivery scheduling, fleet
 restock/replacement coordination, and equipment-safety-concern
 flagging (ALWAYS escalates, never auto-commits at any phase --
 ADR-2607152500 person-facing-service safety guardrail). Three HARD
 governor invariants (asset-unverified, effect-not-propose,
 scope-excluded -- the last folding both the closed 4-op allowlist and
 a content-scan block on directly finalizing/overriding an
 equipment-safety-clearance decision into one check) plus a
 high-cost-threshold escalation on :coordinate-fleet-restock. 49 tests
 / 160 assertions green (clojure -M:dev:test, including
 governor_contract_test.clj's real compiled-graph commit/hard-hold/
 escalate-approve/escalate-reject coverage), clj-kondo 0 errors/0
 warnings, demo runnable end-to-end (clojure -M:dev:run). A nightly
 docs/samples/operator-console.html regenerator
 (.github/workflows/regenerate.yml, hgrentalops.render-html) was
 already present; this fix adds the missing push/PR lint+test gate
 (.github/workflows/ci.yml, sibling-checkout pattern for :dev
 :override-deps, mirrors cloud-itonami-isic-0115/-869/-7710) and sets
 this maturity key.

 KNOWN SCOPE GAP (flagged for a follow-up, not silently closed): this
 repo's own pre-existing docs/business-model.md Trust Controls and
 docs/operator-guide.md Minimum Production Controls name three
 specific hard requirements this landed implementation does not yet
 independently verify as governor checks -- (1) 'agreements cannot be
 released outside verified disclosure scope' (no
 rental-purchase-agreement/disclosure-scope concept or
 :release-rental-agreement-shaped op exists; :log-rental-record's
 free-form :patch could carry TCO-disclosure data but the governor
 does not require or verify it), (2) 'a delivery/pickup without a
 completed condition check' (no independently-verified
 condition-check-completed? gate on :schedule-fleet-operation), (3)
 'reconciliation records require verified evidence' (no reconciliation
 op or evidence-presence check exists). The landed governor instead
 uses a generic equipment-safety-concern framing (defect/damage/
 electrical-hazard) that is a real and legitimate concern but is not
 the same invariant. Extending hgrentalops.governor with these three
 checks (or documenting a deliberate decision not to) is open
 follow-up work, intentionally not done unilaterally on top of another
 session's just-landed, ADR-referenced (ADR-2607152500) design in this
 same fix."}
